Title: Tony Bennett, Lady Gaga celebrate his 96th birthday with Emmy nomination for joint special.
Narrative:
Tony Bennett celebrated his 96th birthday with another Emmy nomination alongside regular partner Lady Gaga!

The Television Academy said Bennett and Lady Gaga, 36, will be individual nominees for their "One Last Time: An Evening with Tony Bennett and Lady Gaga" special, which aired on CBS in November, on the night of his birthday. The programme had previously been confirmed as a nominee for outstanding variety special (pre-recorded), but the names of the musicians were omitted from the nomination because they did not produce it.

The programme was taped over two days, with sold-out performances at New York City's Radio City Music Hall beginning on his 95th birthday.

The Tony Bennett and Lady Gaga special was nominated for five Emmy Awards. It was Bennett's final public appearance before being diagnosed with Alzheimer's disease. He was also nominated for best music video for "Love for Sale".
